        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-06-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-06-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="392" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d392">
                <head>No. 392.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Vignaud</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-06-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 25, 1888</date>. (Received July
                        10.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 628.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Since May 25, date of the new German frontier
                    regulations, over two hundred and fifty passports have been issued by this
                    legation.</p>
                <p>With reference to this subject, I may state for the information of the
                    Department, that according to the German regulations servants must be provided
                    with separate passports.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry Vignaud.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
